Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.94,0:00:03.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Invited by Hattori Heiji and Toyama Kazuha,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.86,0:00:06.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran and I came to Yadori \NVillage in Shizuoka Prefecture
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.51,0:00:09.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to help unearth the buried \Ntreasure of Tokugawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.48,0:00:13.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,However, that night...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.87,0:00:15.08,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's light outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.38,0:00:17.18,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.38,0:00:21.62,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a fire in front of the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.62,0:00:22.50,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.02,0:00:27.04,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Who could've done this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:29.28,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's the nue...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.32,0:00:33.30,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,The nue came in a cloud of black smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.71,0:00:36.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! There's no way \Nanything like that—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.56,0:00:38.90,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Heiji! Look...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.65,0:00:55.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After pursuing the monster, we found...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.29,0:00:57.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.45,0:01:05.09,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's Someji-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.54,0:01:06.98,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Is he unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.53,0:01:10.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.48,0:01:15.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With scratches on his back as though \Nhe was attacked by a wild beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.84,0:01:22.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Curtains rise as the headliner appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.85,0:01:25.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He beautifully dances his \Nmystery-solving steps!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.38,0:01:26.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the Nue or something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.68,0:01:29.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The giant scratches spur the mystery \Nof the buried treasure onward.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.65,0:01:31.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:33.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.48,0:01:35.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.96,0:03:21.97,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(402,1)}Conan and Heiji's Nue Legend \N(Scratch Arc)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.59,0:03:20.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Conan and Heiji's Nue \NLegend, Scratch Arc!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.20,0:03:27.64,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,H-He's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.94,0:03:29.14,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someji-san is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.14,0:03:30.70,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.70,0:03:31.47,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.08,0:03:35.77,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We found him in the trees by \Nthe lake next to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.11,0:03:39.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,He was murdered, with huge \Nscratch marks on his back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.10,0:03:40.95,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.24,0:03:45.28,Fumie,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Masuko Fumie (46) \NAuthor
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.95,0:03:46.83,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Th-They didn't look like \Ntiger claw marks, did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.83,0:03:50.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, they were bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:52.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There were four scratches \Nabout ten centimeters apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.06,0:03:56.53,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You must be joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.53,0:03:58.69,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,This is no joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.35,0:04:00.90,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's the nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:04.34,Hajime,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,222)}Tsurumi Hajime (22) \NDocumentary Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.90,0:04:03.80,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That giant monster got him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.80,0:04:06.52,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}They say the nue has the legs of a tiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.01,0:04:10.52,Michiki,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Tanzawa Michiki (62) \NArchaeologist
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.42,0:04:10.52,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was the jars, but \Nthe monster really does exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.23,0:04:12.02,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.61,0:04:14.65,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing. I was talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.70,0:04:16.90,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,He thought it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:18.40,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...the jars?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.82,0:04:21.02,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you call the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.02,0:04:23.30,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.30,0:04:27.04,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're in the mountains, they \Nsaid they couldn't make it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.04,0:04:31.29,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think the police \Ncan handle a monster like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.46,0:04:33.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.15,0:04:36.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way the monster's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.02,0:04:38.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been some kind of trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.34,0:04:42.30,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I smell kerosene in these burns, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.30,0:04:46.35,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,But you found giant scratches \Non the body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.35,0:04:51.23,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Someji-san probably fled from his attacker \Nafter he was stabbed in the back,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.23,0:04:53.08,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,but he collapsed from exhaustion,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.08,0:04:56.85,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and the culprit made a long \Ncut over the initial wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.12,0:05:01.73,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Then they added three more to make it \Nlook like he'd been attacked by the nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.27,0:05:07.10,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The mayor who invited Someji-san here is \Nprobably the only one who could've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.10,0:05:08.45,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.70,0:05:14.16,Densuke,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Takekuma Densuke (58) \NYadori Village Mayor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.78,0:05:11.70,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The truth is I was asked to \Ninvite everyone by a stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:14.61,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}In addition to the notebook \NI showed you at dinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.61,0:05:18.46,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I was also sent some money and a message \Nstating that inviting the four of them
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.46,0:05:22.57,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,would rekindle the legend of the buried \Ntreasure and revitalize the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:25.30,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Also included were four \Nletters addressed to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.30,0:05:28.12,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,They were guaranteed to come if I sent them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.12,0:05:32.68,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Remember the extra envelope \Nin the letters I sent to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.68,0:05:33.74,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.74,0:05:37.35,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,A letter about the cave-in sixteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.56,0:05:41.48,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,You could be lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:43.80,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.80,0:05:48.13,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The letter even specified which \Nhotel and rooms you should stay in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.13,0:05:49.72,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In any case...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.90,0:05:53.27,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll talk once the police arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.27,0:05:57.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, you'll be staying in your rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.29,0:06:02.75,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll take anything you have that \Ncan make noise like your phones.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.75,0:06:05.23,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Someone may have produced that eerie cry
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.23,0:06:08.09,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,using some kind of device.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.48,0:06:09.67,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.32,0:06:15.78,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,If everyone's rooms were specified \Nlike the mayor said...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.18,0:06:18.89,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe there's something in the rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:22.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Our room was used by the foreigner
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.82,0:06:25.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,who died in the cave-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.07,0:06:27.95,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,I wish someone would switch rooms with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.95,0:06:29.63,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.64,0:06:35.89,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The notebook he used to practice \Nhiragana was in the desk drawer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.26,0:06:39.57,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,There were other notebooks in there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.57,0:06:41.40,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,How interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.40,0:06:44.20,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be willing to swap rooms with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.20,0:06:45.06,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.88,0:06:48.38,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stay in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.82,0:06:52.40,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't allow the women to be frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.35,0:06:56.39,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Then can I move to a room on the third floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.71,0:07:00.10,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind, but don't set one \Nfoot outside of your rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.47,0:07:02.23,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If you do, I'll assume you're the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.43,0:07:06.98,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I see, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.16,0:07:10.24,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,We can see all their rooms from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.24,0:07:14.54,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,And if the monster appears again, \Nwe'll be able to chase it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.54,0:07:17.50,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.50,0:07:19.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You should be staying in your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.35,0:07:22.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You can let us handle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.61,0:07:25.23,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely not. I may \Nhave been told to do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.23,0:07:28.27,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm the one who invited everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.27,0:07:30.96,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,As the mayor, I must \Nensure everyone's safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.96,0:07:34.96,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. As long as you're \Nhere, why don't you tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.96,0:07:36.38,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Tell you what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.38,0:07:38.27,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Why you invited each of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.32,0:07:42.64,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it written in the \Nletter from the stranger?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.92,0:07:44.02,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.53,0:07:47.15,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The archaeologist Tanzawa \NMichiki-san is knowledgeable
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.77,0:07:50.94,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,about the geology of Shizuoka,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:54.28,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,and once examined this area in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.95,0:07:59.63,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,He's excavated ruins not just in \NShizuoka but all over the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.63,0:08:01.62,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Until a few years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.62,0:08:05.04,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,he was famous as a commentator \Non TV programs on ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.55,0:08:08.81,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Although he disappeared \Ncompletely after some pottery
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.81,0:08:11.04,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,he unearthed was suspected of being fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.00,0:08:14.69,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What about the author woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.69,0:08:17.26,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,You mean you don't know who Masuko Fumie is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.17,0:08:22.06,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,She's famous for her mysterious \Nstories featuring monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.32,0:08:27.13,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,As an author of such books, naturally she's \Nknowledgeable about Japanese monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.13,0:08:31.61,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,When filming TV adaptations of her work, \Nshe's had shooting locations changed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:35.24,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,and sets repainted because \Nthey didn't match her vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.50,0:08:40.24,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently she graduated from art school, \Nso I can see why it's so important to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.52,0:08:44.85,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That has nothing to do with \NTokugawa's buried treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.85,0:08:48.02,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The letters suggested using \Nthe nue to revitalize the town,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.02,0:08:50.74,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,if the buried treasure wouldn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.74,0:08:51.85,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.85,0:08:53.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:57.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The documentary reporter isn't famous, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.28,0:08:58.60,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.02,0:09:01.90,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The murdered Someji Yasukatsu-san
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.90,0:09:06.10,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,was a historian knowledgeable about \NTokugawa's buried treasure, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.02,0:09:11.33,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The letter simply stated \Nthat Tsurumi Hajime-san
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.33,0:09:14.98,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,is a fledgling reporter who travels \Nacross the country for monster stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.36,0:09:17.49,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why he was invited either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.22,0:09:23.25,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But why weren't the survivors
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.25,0:09:27.12,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,of the cave-in invited?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.12,0:09:30.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We would've been able to ask \Nthem more about the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.44,0:09:35.59,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,A-Apparently, they all disappeared \Nafter the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.21,0:09:38.24,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even know their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:42.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you invite Heiji-niichan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.44,0:09:44.71,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The letter actually requested that I invite
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.71,0:09:47.89,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,the great detective Mori Kogoro-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.35,0:09:51.90,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,but I used some of the \Nmoney to repair the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.20,0:09:56.51,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,At first I thought about inviting \NKudo Shinichi-sama of Tokyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.51,0:10:00.00,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,but I couldn't get in touch with him, so \NI invited Hattori-sama of Osaka instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.95,0:10:05.50,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm here because the old \Nman and you couldn't make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.50,0:10:06.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.70,0:10:13.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Your letter said I could \Nbring my female friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.56,0:10:16.84,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Was that in the letter \Nfrom the stranger, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.84,0:10:17.47,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.80,0:10:23.16,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The letter said to invite Detective \NMori's daughter as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:28.14,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It would be better for the village's \Npromotional video to have a young girl in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.51,0:10:31.15,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That worked out, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.35,0:10:34.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then there're the trees in front of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.03,0:10:37.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why is only the tree on the left \Nedge different from the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.80,0:10:38.71,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.71,0:10:44.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look. The other trees in front of \Nthe hotel all have pointed tops,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.34,0:10:46.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but just one of them is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.48,0:10:47.62,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.62,0:10:50.88,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't been here in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.80,0:10:54.87,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.38,0:10:59.29,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,There's something that looks like \Ncloth on the end of this burnt stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.66,0:11:03.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was this always in front of the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.21,0:11:04.19,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:05.22,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.85,0:11:07.61,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.61,0:11:08.93,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.39,0:11:12.67,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to take a nap \Nbefore the police arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.67,0:11:16.32,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,but I can't sleep through \Nall the noise you're making!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.32,0:11:18.12,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.02,0:11:22.56,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I'm a talent-less reporter,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.56,0:11:24.57,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,who was invited along with \Nall you famous people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.81,0:11:27.20,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to write a good \Narticle unless I sacrifice sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.20,0:11:29.08,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,to keep my eyes and ears open.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.30,0:11:33.77,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, there's no telling \Nwhen the monster will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.13,0:11:40.42,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's that cry again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.02,0:11:42.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where's it coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.65,0:11:44.34,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.82,0:11:45.82,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd that fire come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.82,0:11:47.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. It suddenly ignited.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.65,0:11:57.76,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,It's the nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.76,0:12:00.99,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,The monster is back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.74,0:12:12.82,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,It's the nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.82,0:12:15.75,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,The monster is back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.37,0:12:21.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What was that scream?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.22,0:12:25.22,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,It sounded like Tanzawa-san \Nfrom the room upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.22,0:12:28.05,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's the room we were \Noriginally staying in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.05,0:12:29.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The left end of the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:31.56,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.84,0:12:33.98,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be able to get \Nin without the spare key.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.64,0:12:45.74,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tanzawa-san! What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.98,0:12:47.72,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tanzawa-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.72,0:12:49.15,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Move, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.15,0:12:50.24,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'll unlock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.08,0:12:53.73,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Tanzawa-san, we're coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.60,0:13:02.89,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. He's already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.08,0:13:08.68,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Two red spots under his chin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.10,0:13:11.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was he bitten by a snake?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.90,0:13:14.43,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the only spare key to this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.43,0:13:16.19,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.38,0:13:18.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means this is a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.43,0:13:22.93,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.73,0:13:25.82,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,the nue really exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.51,0:13:35.58,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.94,0:13:38.75,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Yokomizo Sango of the Shizuoka Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.08,0:13:43.23,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,According to the call we received, \Napparently you saw a giant monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.23,0:13:45.84,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,But now that I'm here, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.84,0:13:48.64,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll protect you from said monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.47,0:13:52.68,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Two people are already dead, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.04,0:13:56.17,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it's some kind of trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.17,0:14:00.94,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,but why don't you tell us what you \Nsaw when you witnessed the monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.86,0:14:06.20,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,We heard an eerie cry,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.20,0:14:08.95,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,and the grass in front \Nof the hotel caught fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.22,0:14:12.33,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,When we went outside, from behind the wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.02,0:14:14.90,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,...a four-legged monster appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.90,0:14:18.83,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was so big, it reached \Nthe second-story windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.12,0:14:21.25,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. And?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.25,0:14:25.52,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see a thin string above the monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.52,0:14:27.34,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't see anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.34,0:14:28.41,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.41,0:14:29.38,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.38,0:14:32.52,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but it bit \Nthe sign in front of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:34.89,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,pulled it out of the ground, \Nand walked away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.06,0:14:38.17,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,It pulled out the sign \Nand walked away with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.17,0:14:41.24,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Was that sign about thirty centimeters tall?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.24,0:14:42.71,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,This is the sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.71,0:14:43.19,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.36,0:14:46.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See? There are teeth marks on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.08,0:14:49.82,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-They're rather large.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.07,0:14:54.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We found this sign on the \Nground where the monster went.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.48,0:14:58.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Next to the sign was a trail \Nof blood leading to the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:15:00.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When we followed it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.16,0:15:04.21,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,we found the body of the \Nhistorian Someji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.90,0:15:08.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With scratches on his back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.49,0:15:11.67,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,S-Scratches? Like from a cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:14.72,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,These are the pictures we took of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.05,0:15:18.91,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,See how the scratches are spaced \Nabout ten centimeters apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.91,0:15:20.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.70,0:15:22.72,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.17,0:15:25.76,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We told everyone to stay in their rooms
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.76,0:15:28.65,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,until the police arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.02,0:15:33.57,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We took their phones so they couldn't \Nproduce any sounds, just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.57,0:15:37.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We were keeping watch over the area
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.08,0:15:41.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the mayor where the monster appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.00,0:15:44.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When we heard the cry again,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.91,0:15:48.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the grass we'd extinguished \Nearlier suddenly caught fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.27,0:15:49.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and it kept spreading and spreading.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.67,0:15:53.89,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,While we were standing\Nin shock, we heard the dying cry
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.89,0:15:58.01,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,of archaeologist Tanzawa-san from\Nthe room on the end of the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.01,0:15:59.53,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When we went to his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.98,0:16:02.85,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,we found him poisoned to \Ndeath in a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.58,0:16:07.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This time with marks under his chin \Nas though he'd been bitten by a snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.82,0:16:09.50,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,C-Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.50,0:16:12.92,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,we saw the monster's tail when it left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.92,0:16:14.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.40,0:16:15.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It looked like a snake, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.98,0:16:16.78,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.03,0:16:18.88,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Its tail was a snake?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.88,0:16:21.31,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Officer, you've heard \Nof the nue, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:25.37,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,It has the head of a monkey, \Nthe body of a raccoon dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.37,0:16:28.67,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,the legs of a tiger, and its tail is a snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.87,0:16:30.54,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The nue?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.54,0:16:35.21,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,It's a legendary monster that appears with \Nan eerie cry and a cloud of black smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.21,0:16:37.05,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,L-Legendary?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.30,0:16:38.97,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't heard of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.97,0:16:41.09,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.09,0:16:45.60,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,You make it sound as though \Nthe monster was resurrected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.54,0:16:50.23,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,But there was once a monster known as the nue
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:52.74,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,that existed in the Kurogane Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.92,0:16:53.99,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.37,0:16:58.50,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,There was an eyewitness report of a nue
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.50,0:17:00.37,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,sixteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.37,0:17:01.79,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.78,0:17:08.38,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The foreigner on the excavation \Nteam was caught in a cave-in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.38,0:17:11.80,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,and wrote the word "nue" before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.22,0:17:14.13,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I've already told them about—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.13,0:17:16.68,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,See? It does exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.95,0:17:21.60,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,The nue's been hiding in the \Nforest for sixteen years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.26,0:17:27.28,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo, this guy's no different \Nfrom that incompetent Gunma cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.28,0:17:28.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.75,0:17:34.06,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, the police will protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.06,0:17:37.36,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,You should gather in a \Nsingle room and wait there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.92,0:17:42.85,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,I will contact my superiors to ask
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.85,0:17:44.66,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,if we can mobilize the self-defense force.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.66,0:17:45.75,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.06,0:17:50.65,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I thought it was going \Nto rain, but it hasn't yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.65,0:17:52.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.51,0:17:57.66,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The second time the grass caught \Nfire, a raindrop fell on my cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.21,0:18:00.14,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I heard
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.14,0:18:05.14,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,the sound of a carbonated \Nbeverage being opened, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.29,0:18:06.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,A carbonated beverage?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.90,0:18:08.81,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.06,0:18:12.73,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,I did request white wine and soda water
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.73,0:18:15.24,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,so I could mix them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.76,0:18:18.82,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,but if I'd poured it from my window,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.82,0:18:21.95,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,the mayor wouldn't have been \Nthe only one who got wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.36,0:18:27.55,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, unlike him, I have more class \Nthan to drink on the window sill.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.55,0:18:29.58,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm so low-class.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.58,0:18:32.76,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,I was abandoned by my \Nparents when I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.76,0:18:35.13,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't raised properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.42,0:18:38.24,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,The water wasn't mine either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.24,0:18:41.63,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I shook my cola as hard as I could,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.63,0:18:44.09,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,it wouldn't have reached the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.09,0:18:45.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji-niichan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.31,0:18:46.09,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.88,0:18:49.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.26,0:18:54.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are small round white \Nobjects all over the grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.76,0:18:58.10,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If this is what I think it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.56,0:19:00.53,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,then even without matches or a lighter...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.00,0:19:02.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...they could've started a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.25,0:19:08.04,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Which leaves the trick \Nbehind the giant monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.45,0:19:11.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...and poisoning in the locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.35,0:19:14.92,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start with the locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.20,0:19:19.12,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim Tanzawa-san moved \Ninto the third floor room
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.12,0:19:22.01,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,we were originally staying in, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.01,0:19:22.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.13,0:19:26.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Based on the positions of their rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.24,0:19:28.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Masuko-san in the room directly \Nbelow his is the most suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.72,0:19:32.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When Tanzawa-san was surprised by the fire \Nand stuck his head out of the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.69,0:19:36.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,she could've thrust a long stick with \Npoisoned needles on the end upwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.50,0:19:41.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason only one side of \Nthe window in that room would open,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.37,0:19:44.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so she could've predicted \Nwhere he'd stick his head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.00,0:19:49.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But when we collected Masuko-san's phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.28,0:19:52.62,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,we examined the room
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.62,0:19:54.71,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and didn't find any sticks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.26,0:19:56.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.40,0:19:58.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The only objects of interest in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.18,0:20:03.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,were the two one liter bottles of soda water,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.79,0:20:08.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,one bottle of white wine, one glass, and the \Nsommelier knife she requested from the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.08,0:20:12.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Inside Masuko-san's bag were writing \Nimplements like ball point pens,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.98,0:20:16.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,paper tape, a sewing set, and a notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.49,0:20:20.66,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What about the documentary writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.66,0:20:23.30,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When Tanzawa-san moved into our room,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.30,0:20:26.99,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,he moved right next door to the \Nthird floor room on the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.50,0:20:31.84,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe only one side of \NTanzawa-san's window opened
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.84,0:20:36.75,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,so it wouldn't block him from shooting \Na poisoned blow dart at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.02,0:20:42.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But Tsurumi-san and Tanzawa-san's \Nwindows were ten meters apart
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.99,0:20:46.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with one window between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.76,0:20:49.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Plus he couldn't pierce the\Nbottom of his chin from the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.88,0:20:52.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And Tsurumi-san didn't have blow darts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.28,0:20:54.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.90,0:20:57.27,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In his room we found
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.90,0:21:01.97,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,three 500 milliliter bottles of cola,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.97,0:21:03.95,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,two bags of potato chips,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.95,0:21:07.93,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,a folding knife, a selfie stick, \Ncigarettes and a lighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.48,0:21:12.16,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and the plastic model he said \Nhe bought to pass the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.87,0:21:15.67,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,He even bought glue.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.02,0:21:20.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't have anything that he \Ncould've used to poison someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.13,0:21:23.82,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Which leaves the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.47,0:21:27.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,All he had was a deck brush.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.50,0:21:32.35,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.98,0:21:35.67,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The police told you to stay inside the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.67,0:21:38.86,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but we're worried about the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.08,0:21:42.17,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,When the nue's cry sounded earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.17,0:21:46.15,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,we heard him barking and \Nscratching at the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.58,0:21:49.91,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,We thought he was hungry \Nand wanted to get out,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.12,0:21:53.17,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,so we made him dinner in the \Nkitchen and brought it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.47,0:21:55.79,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But he won't eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.72,0:22:00.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, when we \Nfirst heard the nue's cry...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.34,0:22:02.30,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,He was barking then, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.67,0:22:06.20,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But when the monster appeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.72,0:22:08.30,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,...he wasn't barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.46,0:22:10.80,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.48,0:22:13.56,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.45,0:22:17.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And the only one who could've done it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.00,0:22:19.28,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,...was that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.01,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.39,0:23:47.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to summon...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.16,0:23:49.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...that monster again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.44,0:23:52.40,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.69,0:23:59.00,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,It's the nue's cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.99,0:24:09.01,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji, where are you? Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.01,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Conan and Heiji's Nue Legend \N(Resolution Arc)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.63,0:24:14.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "Conan and \NHeiji's Nue Legend, Resolution Arc!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:35.03,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Plastic Bottle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.54,0:24:32.59,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.59,0:24:34.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A plastic bottle!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.03,0:24:36.26,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The nue's so scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.03,0:24:40.04,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.26,0:24:37.21,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Where's the self-defense force?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.21,0:24:38.08,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.08,0:24:39.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}We'll extinguish the flames of this case.
